comment.author: 25695066@N00
comment._content: Although the photo itself is marked "YC-125A", the aircraft's registration, NX8500H, reveals it to be the ill-fated Northrop N-23 Pioneer (c/n 2501). This aircraft would serve as the basis for the more powerful Northrop YC-125 Raider (Northrop N-32 Raider), however NX8500H would suffer a fatal crash on February 2, 1948, while testing a new tail configuration. See: aviation-safety.net/wikibase/wiki.php?id=30690
